review:
We were expecting our child since four years of marriage and had seen multiple doctors in Gurgaon and then when my husband relocated to Bangalore on my friends advice we met Dr M Gowri. She is empathetic and kind hearted and quite experienced in her trade. She was almost God send and within a month we were waiting for our 1st child. She gave us excellent guidance all though pregnancy and also during tough times during 3rd trimester where I got admitted once. I am really thankful for her guidance and motherly touch and would recommend her highly!
Regards
Priti Singh

review: I visited Queen's hospital to confirm my pregnancy. I saw that the hospital was fully organized and clean and had all types of facilities for Normal and C-section delivery. After I started visiting here for regular pregnancy checkups. Dr. Gowri madam and the staff treated me very well they took care of me and my baby till last. They heard all our problems and gave solutions. We planned for c-section delivery here. Dr. Gowri who has more than 35 yrs of experience handled every situation very well and took care of me and my baby every day when I got admitted for delivery. My delivery went smoothly and got discharged after 3 days.I recommend this hospital.

******* ****** ** **** ** ***** ** ******

review: I had a wonderful experience with Dr. Gowri throughout my pregnancy. I started visiting her from second month of pregnancy till my delivery. She is very friendly, ************** *** has a lot of experience. At each monthly appointment she would guide me on what to eat and how to take care during pregnancy. she did not suggest any unnecessary tests and prescribed right supplements and medication as per each scan and blood report. I had normal delivery at her hospital. She was very supportive and helpful throughout the process. With her help and guidance i was able to deliver a healthy baby without any complications. I would definitely recommend her to all expecting moms.

Pathetic experience. I went there for a small medical issue, the doctor is okay but the management is pathetic and slow. 

1. Not asking test consent - First the doctor wrote some tests post visitation,then the clinic people directly sent me to the lab room without even asking whether I want to do the tests from the same clinic.
2. Not experienced assistant - The lab technician *** **** ** ***** *** *** **** ******* *** ****** ****** ** kept on moving the needle around my vien to get the blood. When I asked that person whether he is experienced for the job then he said he is from ott and not a lab technician adding to that he took blood on two vials for 3 tests. When I highlighted the same to the receptionist she said not to worry and they will send the reports within 2-3 days. Continued misery
3. Delays and lies - They shared 2 out of 3 test reports and after multiple follow-ups over call/email/whatsapp over a period 8 days they told the 3rd report is not done and advised me to visit the clinic and then they will again do the test.

PATHETIC MANAGEMENT - **** * ******** ALSO THEY DO NOT RESPOND. I AM NEVER GOING THERE AGAIN.

Note - 
1. the follow-up consultation is only free if you visit within 4 days post your 1st consultation.
2. Tests are much cheaper outside the clinic
** ********* *** **** ** *** ** ******* *** ***** ******* **** **** **** ******* ** *** ********
